      <h2 style="font-size:1.09rem; margin: 30px 0 8px 0; font-weight: bold;">
        DAY 1 – URBAN VIBES & HIDDEN GEMS
      </h2>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 28px; font-size:14px;">
        <b>Breakfast at Five Elephant (Kreuzberg)</b><br />
        Kick off your day with specialty coffee and a slice of their famous cheesecake
        at Five Elephant. The café’s relaxed, minimalist design makes it perfect
        to get into a creative workspace, sketch, or just people-watch the streets.<br
        /><br />

        <b>Street art tours & East Side Gallery & YAAM</b><br />
        Join a graffiti tour or stroll along what remains of the East Side Gallery
        – the world’s longest open-air mural. Soak up Berlin’s street art history.
        For lunch and good vibes, relax on the riverside at YAAM (Young African Art
        Market), where graffiti walls, live music, and food stalls create a colorful,
        multicultural atmosphere.<br /><br />

        <b>Co-working hubs & boutiques (Kreuzberg)</b><br />
        If you’re into focus zones with an artsy open-space vibe, grab a pass at
        betahaus. This co-working hub buzzes with young programmers, designers, and
        makers. Their green courtyard and affordable vegan snacks and smoothies are
        perfect for recharging mid-day.<br /><br />

        <b>Lunch at Burgermesiter</b><br />
        Located in the railway tracks in Kreuzberg, Burgermeister serves some of
        the city’s best burgers from what used to be a public restroom – quirky,
        raw, and very Berlin.<br /><br />

        <b>Afternoon at Voo Store & Five Elephant (Neukölln)</b><br />
        Time for shopping and more treats at Five Elephant in Neukölln. The iconic
        1960s building has serene vintage charm. It is both bright and clean, with
        interiors that feel straight out of a design magazine.
      </div>
      <img
        src="https://picsum.photos/700/280?berlin2"
