      <h2 style="font-size:1.09rem; margin: 30px 0 8px 0; font-weight: bold;">
        DAY 2 – ART, CULTURE & CHILL
      </h2>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 28px; font-size:14px;">
        <b>Morning coffee at The Barn (Mitte)</b><br />
        Start your second day at The Barn, one of Berlin’s most famous roasteries.
        Their industrial-chic café is popular with designers and students who want
        to sip coffee and sketch ideas while people-watching.<br /><br />

        <b>Art: König Galerie & Hamburger Bahnhof</b><br />
        Spend your late morning exploring König Galerie, a innovative contemporary
        art gallery housed in a converted Brutalist church. For something heady,
        check out Hamburger Bahnhof (Berlin’s Museum for Actual Art), where you’ll
        want to sketch by Andy Warhol, Joseph Beuys, and rising European talent.<br
        /><br />

        <b>Afternoon at Mauerpark</b><br />
        Sundays in Mauerpark are legendary. Browse the market stalls for vintage
        clothes, flip through old magazines, or just sit on the grass while live
        musicians strum away. If you’re brave, step up on the karaoke stage – Berlin
        tradition!<br /><br />

        <b>Close the day: Klunkerkranich (Neukölln rooftop)</b><br />
        End the day with dinner near Neukölln’s Heimathafen, a buzzing indoor market
        hall. On street food nights, head up to the Klunkerkranich rooftop and set
        up while snacking, mix art installations and exciting nightlife.<br
        /><br />

        <b>Nightlife tip: Berghain Kantine or Sisyphos</b><br />
        If you want the classic Berlin experience, dip into the notorious Berghain
        queues, try Sisyphos for something more chill and décor is stylish. Sisyphos
        is a converted club with art markets and music stages. Both are popular with
        the creative crowd.
      </div>
