      <h2 style="font-size:1.09rem; margin: 30px 0 8px 0; font-weight: bold;">
        INSIDER & BUDGET TIPS
      </h2>
      <ul style="font-size:14px; margin-bottom: 26px;">
        <li>
          Many galleries (like Hamburger Bahnhof) offer free entry on Thursdays
          after 6 pm.
        </li>
        <li>
          Berlin’s metro app NextStop is great for indie-friendly creative
          routes through overlooked neighborhoods.
        </li>
        <li>
          Pack a smartphone, charger, and notebook – grab a 48-hour ticket for
          unlimited U-Bahn and trams all zones.
        </li>
        <li>
          Make room design books and zines, don’t miss old mural itself in
          Mitte’s creative bookshops (book shopping is an art and vacation
          ritual…)
        </li>
      </ul>
      <div
        style="font-size:13px; color:#444; max-width:640px; margin:auto; text-align:center;"
      >
        Two days in Berlin will only scratch the surface, but by focusing on
        creative spaces, local cafés, and quirky hangouts, you’ll learn to fall
        in love the city very gently. Berlin is place where art is everywhere –
        on the walls, in the clubs, in the food market – and it’s the perfect
        escape for young creatives looking to recharge and get inspired.
      </div>
